---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
import CtaBand from "../../components/CtaBand.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="SYAG vs. Guard Management Software — What Guard Software Misses"
  description="Guard software tracks your guards. SYAG runs your entire facility. See why TrackTik, Silvertrac, and Belfry leave 80% of your security operations unaddressed."
>
  <PageHero
    label="SYAG vs. Guard Software"
    headline="Guard software manages your guards. SYAG manages your facility."
    subheadline="Guard management tools are good at what they do: scheduling, GPS tracking, patrol verification, and incident reporting. But they were built for security contracting companies — not for facility operators. And they cover less than 20% of your facility's security signals."
  />

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">What happens when you only have guard software</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">You've deployed a guard management tool. Your guards are tracked, patrols are logged, and incidents are filed from mobile. Good.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">But:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>Your cameras don't know your guards exist. Camera events sit in a separate VMS dashboard. When a motion alarm fires, no one is automatically notified. No incident is created. No guard is dispatched.</li>
        <li>Your IoT devices — panic buttons, sensors, UPS monitors — aren't integrated anywhere. They alert to a separate system, if they alert at all.</li>
        <li>Your assets are still on a spreadsheet. Your visitor register is still paper. Your incident reports live in a separate system from your patrol logs.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">The result: you have operational data in four or five places — no unified picture of your facility.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">What guard software covers — and what it doesn't</h2>
    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10">
      <table class="w-full text-left text-sm text-white/70">
        <thead class="bg-white/5 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Capability</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">TrackTik</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Silvertrac</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Belfry</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-semibold">SYAG</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/10">
          {[
            ["Guard scheduling & GPS", "✓", "✓", "✓", "✓"],
            ["Patrol & checkpoint verification", "✓", "✓", "✓", "✓"],
            ["Mobile incident reporting", "✓", "✓", "✓", "✓"],
            ["Camera / VMS integration", "✗", "✗", "✗", "✓"],
            ["IoT device management", "✗", "✗", "✗", "✓"],
            ["Asset management", "✗", "✗", "✗", "✓"],
            ["Visitor management", "✗", "✗", "✗", "✓"],
            ["Visual flow automation", "✗", "✗", "✗", "✓"],
            ["Multi-tenant SaaS", "✓", "Partial", "✓", "✓"],
            ["MEA-native, Arabic support", "✗", "✗", "✗", "✓"],
          ].map(([cap, tt, ss, bf, syag]) => (
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white/60">{cap}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">{tt}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">{ss}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">{bf}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-semibold">{syag}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">The cost of the gap</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">When you use guard management software, you still need:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>A VMS or NVR for cameras: {"{$500–2,000/month}"}</li>
        <li>IoT monitoring software or manual monitoring: {"{staff time + tools}"}</li>
        <li>Asset tracking (spreadsheet or dedicated tool): {"{staff time}"}</li>
        <li>Visitor management (paper register or separate app): {"{staff time}"}</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Add these up and compare to SYAG's single subscription. The economics change quickly.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Guard software does its job well — for guard companies</h2>
    <div class="glass-card">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        TrackTik, Silvertrac, and Belfry are excellent tools for security contracting companies that
        need to manage large guard workforces across multiple client sites, handle scheduling and
        payroll, and prove service delivery to clients.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-white/60">
        If you are a facility manager — not a security company — your needs are different. You don't
        need billing, payroll, or client portals. You need a unified operational picture of your facility.
        That's what SYAG is.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    headline="See exactly what SYAG covers that guard software doesn't."
    primaryLabel="Request a demo →"
    primaryHref="/demo"
  />
</Layout>
